        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 3:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 259 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Canadian, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canadian, Glazier, and Lake Marvin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
